CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1969, pg. 16 reads: "Kappa For Life - Dr. William "Stud" Greene, former Grand Polemach [sic] of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity of Washington, D.C. (right), is shown presenting a pin and plaque to local Polemarch George Charlton, in recognition of Charlton's lief membership in the fraternity.  Presentation was made at the Pittsburgh Chapter's annual Founder's Day"
TitMainTitle: George Charlton, receiving Life Membership Award from Dr. Henry "Stud" Green, standing in Stouffers Restaurant, for Kappa Alpha Psi founders Day banquet
